extends Object
implements BaseGraphFactory<TemporalGraphHead,TemporalVertex,TemporalEdge,TemporalGraph,TemporalGraphCollection>
    Responsible for creating instances of TemporalGraph based on a specific layout.

      • fromNonTemporalDataSets

        public TemporalGraph fromNonTemporalDataSets(org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<? extends GraphHead> graphHead,
                                             org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<? extends Vertex> vertices,
                                             org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<? extends Edge> edges)
        Creates a TemporalGraph instance by the given EPGM graph head, vertex and edge datasets. The method assumes that the given vertices and edges are already assigned to the given graph head.
        Parameters:
        graphHead - 1-element graph head DataSet
        vertices - vertex DataSet
        edges - edge DataSet
        Returns:
        a temporal graph with default temporal data

      • fromNonTemporalDataSets

        public <G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge> TemporalGraph fromNonTemporalDataSets(org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<G> graphHead,
                                                                                                   TimeIntervalExtractor<G> graphHeadTimeIntervalExtractor,
                                                                                                   org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<V> vertices,
                                                                                                   TimeIntervalExtractor<V> vertexTimeIntervalExtractor,
                                                                                                   org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<E> edges,
                                                                                                   TimeIntervalExtractor<E> edgeTimeIntervalExtractor)
        Creates a TemporalGraph instance. By the provided timestamp extractors, it is possible to extract temporal information from the data to define a timestamp or time interval that represents the beginning and end of the element's validity (valid time). The method assumes that the given vertices and edges are already assigned to the given graph head.
        Type Parameters:
        G - The graph head type.
        V - The vertex type.
        E - The edge type.
        Parameters:
        graphHead - 1-element graph head DataSet
        graphHeadTimeIntervalExtractor - extractor to pick the time interval from graph heads
        vertices - vertex DataSet
        vertexTimeIntervalExtractor - extractor to pick the time interval from vertices
        edges - edge DataSet
        edgeTimeIntervalExtractor - extractor to pick the time interval from edges
        Returns:
        a temporal graph with temporal data extracted using extractor functions

      • fromNonTemporalGraph

        public TemporalGraph fromNonTemporalGraph(BaseGraph<?,?,?,?,?> graph)
        Creates a TemporalGraph instance from a (non-temporal) base graph. This method calls fromNonTemporalDataSets(DataSet, DataSet, DataSet) on the graphs element data sets.
        Parameters:
        graph - Some base graph.
        Returns:
        The resulting temporal graph.
